title: Kayleigh McEnany On President Trump Challenging Vote Counting Procedures & Republicans Picking Up Seats In The House
summary:
Kayleigh McEnany, Trump Campaign Senior Advisor, spoke with Brian Kilmeade about President Trump wanting to make sure only legal votes are being counted in battleground states.
Kayleigh discussed the pending litigation in Nevada focusing on out of state voters and their belief President Trump will win in Georgia because of the overseas military ballots that have yet to be counted.
McEnany also discussed President Trump being encouraged with republicans picking up seats in the House and keeping the Senate.
McEnany said President Trump has won more voters of color than any republican since 1960 and has a very proud legacy of making the republican party the party of the American worker.
